r linear barcodes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbarcodeformatdatabarexpandedconfiguration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"GS1 DataBar Expanded barcode configuration. Add to scanner configuration to scan GS1 DataBar Expanded and GS1 DataBar Expanded Stacked barcodes."}],"title":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBarcodeFormatDataBarExpandedConfiguration/initWithRegexFilter:minimumSizeScore:addAdditionalQuietZone:minimum1DQuietZoneSize:minimumNumberOfRequiredFramesWithEqua